    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix positioning information request decoding logic\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was missing from the current codebase, causing issues with NRPPa message handling. When attempting to decode positioning information requests, the system would fail to find the required functions.\n\nThis fix reintroduces the positioning functionality and corrects the decoding logic in `decode_positioning_information_req`. The original implementation had redundant processing of mandatory IEs and delayed type validation, which could lead to inconsistent behavior when handling malformed messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Reimplemented positioning message encoding/decoding functions\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Added positioning function declarations\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/CMakeLists.txt`: Added positioning files to build\n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added positioning information request structure\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Attempt to call `decode_positioning_information_req()` with a valid F1AP PDU containing positioning information request\n2. Observe that function is not found due to missing implementation\n3. With fix applied, function correctly decodes mandatory IEs and validates types immediately\n\nThe fix ensures that mandatory IEs are validated for both presence and correct type immediately upon discovery, rather than processing them twice as in the original implementation.\n"
}